%N A202100 Square array read by antidiagonals: T(n,k) = Number of (n+2) X (k+2) binary arrays avoiding patterns 001 and 011 in rows and columns.
%H A202100 R. H. Hardin, <a href="/A202100/b202100.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..544</a>
%H A202100 Christian Krause, <a href="/A202093/a202093.txt">Proof of formula</a>, Jun 26 2026
%F A202100 T(n,k) = C(alpha+E, E) * C(alpha+O, O) * C(beta+E, E) * C(beta+O, O) where C = binomial, alpha = ceiling((n+2)/2), beta = floor((n+2)/2), E = ceiling((k+2)/2) and O = floor((k+2)/2). - _Zhuorui He_, Jun 29 2026
